Verplank Takes 2-Shot Lead at Golf’s PGA Championship, Woods May Miss Cut

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-08-12T20:53:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/verplank-takes-2-shot-lead-at-golf-s-pga-championship-woods-may-miss-cut.html
Scott Verplank has taken a two-shot
lead during the second round at the U.S. PGA Championship.   Verplank is 6-under par at Atlanta Athletic Club in Johns
Creek,  Georgia , and 3-under through eight holes of his second
round at the season’s final major tournament.  Steve Stricker , who entered the day with a two-shot lead,
has fallen to 4-under for the tournament. He’s 3-over par
through nine holes in the second round and tied for second with
 Adam Scott , D.A. Points and Brandt Jobe.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  